results.lead_paragraph: " Give me a place to stand and I will move the earth." Archimedes, as reported at the time, made his celebrated statement with a simplicity and directness never achieved by Homer or the Greek dramatists studied in the schools: "Dos moi pousto kai kino ten gen" -- "Give me where I stand and I will move the earth."
